\par
## Lesson 9.8: Size \f1\endash  Being Larger Than Life While Truthful\par
\par
**Size** (Adler's term) refers to the expansion of the actor's presence, voice, and energy to fill the theatrical space while remaining absolutely truthful.\par
\par
**The Principle:**\par
- Stage acting requires more than "real life" behavior\par
- The back row must see and feel you\par
- But "bigger" does not mean "false" or "exaggerated"\par
- Size comes from commitment, not volume\par
\par
**How to Achieve Size:**\par
- Commit fully to every action (half-commitment reads as small)\par
- Use your entire body (not just your face and voice)\par
- Breathe fully and deeply\par
- Allow your voice to resonate (don't hold back)\par
- Trust that truth can be large\par
\par
**Size on Film vs. Stage:**\par
\par
| Medium | Size Requirement |\par
|--------|------------------|\par
| *Stage (large theatre)* | Very large; the back row needs to see you |\par
| *Stage (small theatre)* | Moderate; truthful but present |\par
| *Film (close-up)* | Very small; the camera sees everything |\par
| *Film (wide shot)* | Similar to stage; gesture reads |\par
\par
\f2\u-10179?\u-9002?\f1  \f0 **Adler**: "Size is not shouting. Size is being fully alive."\par
\par
