\par
## Lesson 9.11: How Often to Practice Meisner Repetition\par
\par
Sanford Meisner recommended **daily practice** of the repetition exercise with a partner.\par
\par
**Recommended Practice Schedule:**\par
\par
| Frequency | Duration | Focus |\par
|-----------|----------|-------|\par
| *Daily* | 15-30 minutes | Basic repetition, no variations |\par
| *Weekly* | 1 hour | Advanced repetition with activities |\par
| *Monthly* | 2-3 hours | Repetition in scene work |\par
\par
**What Consistent Practice Develops:**\par
- Spontaneous, authentic responses\par
- Deep listening and attention\par
- Freedom from planning and control\par
- Trust in your instincts\par
- Ability to be affected by your partner\par
\par
**How to Practice Alone:**\par
While repetition requires a partner, you can practice:\par
- Independent Activities (doing truthful tasks)\par
- Sensory recall (remembering sensory details)\par
- Public solitude (concentrating while being watched)\par
\par
\f2\u-10179?\u-9002?\f1  \f0 **Meisner**: "Don't think about it. Just do it. Every day."\par
\par
